==English==
{{wikipedia}}

===Etymology===
Sense of “what is {{l|en|added}}” dating from 14th Century {{C.E.}}; from {{etyl|fro|en}} {{term|adition||increasement|lang=fro}}, from {{etyl|la|en}} {{term|additionem||lang=la}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/əˈdɪʃn̩/|/əˈdɪʃən/}}, {{X-SAMPA|1=/@"dISn=/|2=/@"dIS@n/}}
* {{audio|en-us-addition.ogg|Audio (US)}}
* {{rhymes|ɪʃən}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun|s|-}}

# {{uncountable}} The act of adding anything.
#: ''The addition of five more items to the agenda will make the meeting unbearably long.''
# Anything that is added.
# {{uncountable}} The [[arithmetic operation]] of [[add]]ing.

